---
import PublicLayout from '@/layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Springbok Expeditions"
  description="Springbok Expeditions privacy policy. How we collect, use, and protect your personal data."
>
  <section class="section bg-dusk-50">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow text-safari-600 mb-3">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-display-sm md:text-display-md font-display font-medium tracking-tight text-safari-900 mb-4">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-dusk-500 mb-8">Last updated: January 2026</p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-dusk-100 p-8 md:p-10 space-y-8 text-dusk-700 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Springbok Expeditions ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting the privacy of our customers and website visitors. This policy describes what personal data we collect, how we use it, who we share it with, and the rights you have over your data.
        </p>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">1. Who we are</h2>
          <p>Springbok Expeditions is a Tanzania-based tour operator. Our office is in Arusha, and we operate under the laws of the United Republic of Tanzania. You can contact our data team at <a href="mailto:info@springbokexpeditions.com" class="text-safari-700 underline hover:text-safari-900">info@springbokexpeditions.com</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">2. What data we collect</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">We collect the minimum data needed to plan and run your trip:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Contact information (name, email, phone, postal address)</li>
            <li>Travel documents (passport number, nationality, date of birth - needed for park and flight bookings)</li>
            <li>Health and dietary information you share with us (only as needed for the trip)</li>
            <li>Payment information (processed by our payment provider - we do not store card numbers)</li>
            <li>Website usage data (pages visited, referrer, basic device info - via standard analytics)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">3. How we use your data</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>To plan, quote, and book your trip</li>
            <li>To communicate with you about your trip (and only that - we do not buy mailing lists or sell data)</li>
            <li>To meet our legal and tax obligations</li>
            <li>To improve our website (via aggregated, anonymised analytics)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">4. Who we share data with</h2>
          <p>We share the minimum needed to deliver your trip, with:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>Lodges, camps, and other ground suppliers (your name and stay dates)</li>
            <li>Internal flight operators (full name, passport number, date of birth - as required by the airline)</li>
            <li>National park authorities (your name and park fees - required for entry)</li>
            <li>Our payment processor (card details at the point of payment - never stored by us)</li>
            <li>Our email service (Resend) for booking confirmations and pre-trip information</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">We do not sell, rent, or trade your data. We do not share it with marketing partners.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">5. Cookies and analytics</h2>
          <p>Our website uses a minimal set of cookies - for session management and (if you opt in) for privacy-respecting analytics via Plausible. We do not use Google Analytics, Facebook tracking, or any advertising cookies.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">6. Data retention</h2>
          <p>We keep your trip data for 7 years (required for tax and insurance purposes), then delete it. You can ask us to delete it sooner - see your rights below.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">7. Your rights</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">You can ask us at any time to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Provide a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li>Correct any data that is wrong</li>
            <li>Delete your data (subject to the 7-year retention above)</li>
            <li>Stop sending you marketing communications (we send very few - typically one or two a year)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">Email <a href="mailto:info@springbokexpeditions.com" class="text-safari-700 underline hover:text-safari-900">info@springbokexpeditions.com</a> and we will respond within 30 days.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">8. Security</h2>
          <p>We use HTTPS, encrypted password storage, and limited access controls on our systems. No system is 100% secure, but we work hard to protect your data and respond quickly to any incident.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-safari-900 mb-3">9. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>If we change this policy in a material way, we will email you and update the date at the top. Small changes (typos, clarifications) will be made without notification.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PublicLayout>
